Module 1: The Regret Minimization Engine
Concept: Optimize for minimum regret, not maximum outcome.
TRADITIONAL: "Which strategy gives best outcome?"

YOUR APPROACH: "Which strategy makes me regret least if I'm wrong?"

ANALYSIS:
Strategy A: Best case +50%, Worst case -10% â†’ Regret if chosen: Low
Strategy B: Best case +60%, Worst case -30% â†’ Regret if chosen: High
Strategy C: Best case +40%, Worst case +10% â†’ Regret if chosen: Lowest âœ“

RECOMMENDATION: Strategy C (Regret-minimizing)
"Even in worst case, we still get 10% improvement. 
 In best case, we get 40%â€”slightly less upside but much safer."
Why this matters:
Real executives are risk-averse. They'd rather have a guaranteed 40% improvement than gamble on 60% with 30% downside risk.
